1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:03,510
(Episode 49)

2
00:00:16,960 --> 00:00:20,430
I'm not going anywhere, Mom.
Please let go. Okay?

3
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:24,630
No. Ok Hee and Tok Hee are
Suk Hee's daughters.

4
00:00:24,860 --> 00:00:27,500
Ok Hee and Tok Hee can't disappear.

5
00:00:36,170 --> 00:00:38,440
If you have any idea how Mom is feeling,

6
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,610
you can't forgive Chae Hwa Young.

7
00:00:42,150 --> 00:00:45,980
She's the one who raised me for 30 years.
She's a mother to me.

8
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:48,520
I've had enough. Let's go, right now.

9
00:00:48,590 --> 00:00:50,720
- Let's expose everything. Now!
- Shit!

10
00:00:51,060 --> 00:00:52,090
Let go of me.

11
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:54,630
Give me the evidence.
Hand it over right now!

12
00:00:55,990 --> 00:00:59,660
Jang Mi. You're upsetting Tok Hee.
Stop it.

13
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,370
Mom, you don't even know anything!

14
00:01:05,740 --> 00:01:07,640
Why do you think I suggested
we trade places?

15
00:01:08,010 --> 00:01:09,270
I already told you.

16
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:12,010
I couldn't bring myself to turn in
the woman who raised me,

17
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:13,650
so I left it up to you.

18
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:17,020
Can't you just give me one day of peace?

19
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:21,490
After today, I won't just be
the ordinary Ma Seo Rin anymore.

20
00:01:22,050 --> 00:01:25,160
The woman who raised me
is an infant kidnapper...

21
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,490
and a murderer who tried to kill
my birth mother.

22
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:43,710
Shit! What's going on?
Did Mom already catch on?

23
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,310
We can't get caught right now.

24
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:48,250
If we get caught, it's all for nothing.

25
00:01:48,510 --> 00:01:50,350
Oh Jang Mi, just get through tonight.

26
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:53,690
Otherwise, I'm dead. I will die!

27
00:01:55,090 --> 00:01:56,990
- The evidence?
- I'll give it to you tomorrow.

28
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,890
Meet me there at 12 p.m.

29
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:04,030
- You'll really give it to me?
- I said I would!

30
00:02:04,330 --> 00:02:05,360
So just go already.

31
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,770
Just go already, please!

32
00:02:16,140 --> 00:02:19,010
Mom, it's cold. Let's go home now.

33
00:02:20,010 --> 00:02:22,710
- Ok Hee's not here.
- She said she'd be back tomorrow.

34
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:24,820
When Oh Jang Mi comes tomorrow,

35
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:27,190
let's all get together again, okay?

36
00:02:27,990 --> 00:02:29,020
Really?

37
00:02:29,490 --> 00:02:30,720
Suk Hee is so excited!

38
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:34,830
Wonderful! Let's go!

39
00:02:58,950 --> 00:03:00,850
Have you been well?

40
00:03:02,050 --> 00:03:03,920
You look more beautiful than ever.

41
00:03:05,460 --> 00:03:07,060
It must have been difficult for you.

42
00:03:07,390 --> 00:03:09,360
The hardest part was
not being able to see you.

43
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:11,500
There was nothing more difficult...

44
00:03:12,930 --> 00:03:13,930
than that.

45
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:17,740
I have to get Jun Ho and Seo Rin married.

46
00:03:18,570 --> 00:03:20,570
That's the only way
my dream can come true.

47
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:22,440
Professor,

48
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:24,810
we...

49
00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:26,840
have to break up.

50
00:03:28,050 --> 00:03:31,620
Don't say that.
Hwa Young, are you upset with me?

51
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:35,650
There were so many things I wanted
to tell you when we finally met.

52
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:40,490
I was worried it might cause you trouble,

53
00:03:41,290 --> 00:03:45,230
so I forced myself to endure
not seeing you all this time.

54
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:47,500
It was purely...

55
00:03:48,670 --> 00:03:51,500
because I wanted to protect you so badly.

56
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,170
I understand your heart, Professor.

57
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:57,240
Then how can you say you want to break up
the second we finally meet?

58
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:02,710
I can't do it.

59
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:04,720
I can't break up with you.

60
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:11,460
Look me in the eye.

61
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,360
Hwa Young,

62
00:04:14,990 --> 00:04:17,200
do you want to live without me?

63
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:28,440
See?

64
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:32,480
You don't want to leave me either, do you?

65
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:37,050
Let's not worry about the future.

66
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:39,150
Just like this,

67
00:04:40,350 --> 00:04:42,450
let's see this through to the very end.

68
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:55,530
<i>- For you, just for tonight</i>
- Mom, what are you doing?

69
00:04:56,370 --> 00:04:57,470
Can't you tell by looking?

70
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:01,540
Your dad has to start teaching again,

71
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:05,640
so I'm polishing his shoes
so they'll sparkle.

72
00:05:05,710 --> 00:05:09,910
<i>You, who must leave when tomorrow comes</i>

73
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:14,350
<i>Staring into your sad eyes</i>

74
00:05:14,820 --> 00:05:16,150
Yes, this is Kang Baek Ho speaking.

75
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:17,660
Who is this?

76
00:05:19,390 --> 00:05:21,490
It's me, Jang Mi.

77
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:23,130
Jang Mi?

78
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,260
Whose phone is this?

79
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,530
I'm out right now,

80
00:05:28,570 --> 00:05:30,840
so I borrowed someone's phone to call you.

81
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,300
Really?

82
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:36,410
Have you already thought of your wish?
What is it?

83
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,680
My wish?

84
00:05:40,180 --> 00:05:42,710
Actually, Baek Ho,

85
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:45,280
can you come pick me up?

86
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:52,260
Where are you going at this hour?

87
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:53,960
A friend just called
with something urgent.

88
00:05:54,030 --> 00:05:56,690
You're meeting Oh Jang Mi, aren't you?

89
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:58,700
- I'll be back.
- Baek Ho!

90
00:05:59,260 --> 00:06:01,200
Goodness,

91
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,970
he's so head over heels
that he can't think straight.

92
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,640
Jang Mi?

93
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:16,110
Why do you look so beautiful?

94
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:18,180
You're not wearing your glasses either.

95
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,890
Is that really you, Jang Mi?

96
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:24,360
Did you go on a blind date
behind my back or something?

97
00:06:25,690 --> 00:06:26,690
I just...

98
00:06:27,290 --> 00:06:29,830
dressed up because I was meeting you.

99
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:31,230
And I put in contacts, too.

100
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:35,600
You look like
a completely different person.

101
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:45,040
But what's going on?

102
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:47,210
Nothing really.

103
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:50,010
I just wanted to see you.

104
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:53,750
Right. Have you decided on your wish?

105
00:06:57,890 --> 00:06:58,890
My wish?

106
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:02,060
Baek Ho.

107
00:07:03,260 --> 00:07:04,930
I feel so suffocated.

108
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:08,670
I really need to get some fresh air.

109
00:07:35,090 --> 00:07:36,090
Chae Hwa Young.

110
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:39,730
Were you the one
who caused my father's death?

111
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:44,800
My dad went to Dream Hotel
and found out that we were twins.

112
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:47,170
So, Chae Hwa Young,

113
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:49,870
are you the one who killed my father?

114
00:08:03,890 --> 00:08:05,020
It's cold out, Jang Mi.

115
00:08:07,190 --> 00:08:08,190
Baek Ho...

116
00:08:42,830 --> 00:08:45,230
Wait, she left earlier
and still hasn't come back?

117
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,230
Where on earth did she go?

118
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,120
Jang Mi,

119
00:09:10,190 --> 00:09:11,320
I'll protect you.

120
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:14,060
Don't worry about a thing and sleep.

121
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:16,560
I'm sorry,

122
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,260
and I love you, Jang Mi.

123
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:39,150
What? Her car's gone, too?

124
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,390
And you don't know where she went?

125
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:45,860
Where in the world
did Seo Rin disappear to?

126
00:09:46,060 --> 00:09:47,860
I'll have all my men look for her.

127
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:49,790
Find her now!

128
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:53,030
Seo Rin was acting so strange today.

129
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:57,500
Yes, ma'am. We'll search the city tonight
for any place she might have gone.

130
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:00,000
You have to find Seo Rin.

131
00:10:03,510 --> 00:10:05,910
Who in the world was she talking to
on the phone?

132
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,250
This is so comfortable.

133
00:10:23,090 --> 00:10:27,470
<i>Rock-a-bye, rock-a-bye, Ok Hee, Tok Hee</i>

134
00:10:28,730 --> 00:10:32,600
<i>You're sleeping so soundly,</i>
<i>my little Tok Hee</i>

135
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:35,310
Ok Hee, Tok Hee?

136
00:10:36,370 --> 00:10:40,410
<i>Rock-a-bye, rock-a-bye, my Tok Hee.</i>

137
00:10:47,020 --> 00:10:48,190
Go to sleep now.

138
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:18,120
Baek Ho's eyelashes are so long.

139
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,500
What are you doing?

140
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:42,040
Were you staring at me this whole time
while I was asleep?

141
00:11:42,370 --> 00:11:43,370
Just like I was.

142
00:11:44,610 --> 00:11:45,610
What was that?

143
00:11:46,210 --> 00:11:48,910
You were watching me sleep, too?

144
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:51,020
Of course.

145
00:11:51,350 --> 00:11:54,390
You looked so beautiful sleeping.
I just stared for the longest time.

146
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:01,490
The sun's already coming up.

147
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:05,800
It's a shame we have to leave.

148
00:12:07,530 --> 00:12:09,670
If you ever need to clear your head again,
just say the word.

149
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:12,800
I'll be there in a flash to pick you up.

150
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:16,370
Thank you.

151
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:36,090
Yes, what is it?

152
00:12:36,090 --> 00:12:38,200
Ma'am, we have a huge problem.

153
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:41,130
A huge problem?

154
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:44,570
Don't tell me something happened
to Seo Rin.

155
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:09,290
Did something happen at the hotel?

156
00:13:09,490 --> 00:13:12,030
We're suddenly short on rooms
for the foreign VIPs...

157
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:14,930
for the international forum
starting in Seoul today.

158
00:13:15,130 --> 00:13:18,470
The forum organizers have requested...

159
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:20,470
more rooms on the hotel's VIP floor.

160
00:13:20,740 --> 00:13:22,640
Is Seo Rin back yet?

161
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:25,510
Yes. She said she couldn't sleep
last night,

162
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:28,250
so it looks like she went to sleep
in one of our hotel suites.

163
00:13:28,650 --> 00:13:30,050
I think she just got back.

164
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:33,480
Okay, as long as she's back.
That's a relief.

165
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:35,420
I'm sorry for worrying you, Father.

166
00:13:35,620 --> 00:13:38,460
Then hurry to the office
and fix this problem...

167
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:41,290
about the VIP double-booking situation.

168
00:13:41,990 --> 00:13:43,930
If any issues
with the forum VIPs come up now,

169
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:46,330
it could blow up into a diplomatic
and shareholder issue, right?

170
00:13:46,330 --> 00:13:47,870
Yes, I'll get right on it.

171
00:13:47,930 --> 00:13:51,070
Oh, my. Then that's a huge problem.

172
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:55,040
Work it out with our other guests.

173
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:56,110
Yes.

174
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:13,720
What is it?

175
00:14:17,130 --> 00:14:20,360
Seo Rin has been drinking
way too much lately,

176
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,430
and I think it's time I ground her.

177
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:26,400
Watch her closely
and don't let her leave the house.

178
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:27,810
Me?

179
00:14:27,870 --> 00:14:29,770
You're the one lounging around at home.

180
00:14:29,770 --> 00:14:31,340
You expect me to do it while I'm working?

181
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,550
And tell Mrs. Yang
to keep an eye on her, too.

182
00:14:35,310 --> 00:14:37,780
Goodness. All right.

183
00:14:37,780 --> 00:14:38,820
Go on, then.

184
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:02,440
Oh Jang Mi.

185
00:15:03,070 --> 00:15:06,740
Why are you sleeping in so late?
Get up and eat breakfast.

186
00:15:07,650 --> 00:15:09,610
I don't eat breakfast, you know that.

187
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:12,120
That's ridiculous.

188
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,720
Since when do you not eat breakfast?

189
00:15:14,220 --> 00:15:17,250
You never skip breakfast, no matter what.
What's gotten into you?

190
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:20,890
- Oh Jang Mi.
- Yes, Oh Jang Mi.

191
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:22,830
Take this protest of yours down a notch.

192
00:15:23,430 --> 00:15:25,230
You think I accepted
that settlement for myself?

193
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,300
I did it so our family could get by.

194
00:15:44,980 --> 00:15:46,480
I slept like a rock.

195
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:49,950
I feel so refreshed.

196
00:15:59,460 --> 00:16:01,670
Just because you can't sleep,

197
00:16:01,670 --> 00:16:04,800
you can't just get a suite at the hotel.

198
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:06,370
Got it, Seo Rin?

199
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,570
- Okay.
- Why didn't you take a sleeping pill?

200
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:13,740
- I'm trying to go without them.
- And what's the point of that?

201
00:16:14,210 --> 00:16:18,320
Your mom says you're drinking too much,
so she's grounding you starting today.

202
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,820
Grounded? Is this a military boot camp?

203
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:24,760
She told me I have to stay here
and watch you.

204
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:28,390
So now I'm stuck here on guard duty.
Unbelievable.

205
00:16:36,070 --> 00:16:38,800
That's weird. Why isn't she talking back?

206
00:16:39,270 --> 00:16:42,070
Your mother had to leave early
for work this morning.

207
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:45,480
She was up all night worrying about you
and left without any sleep, you brat.

208
00:16:46,140 --> 00:16:47,710
I'm sorry, Grandfather.

209
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:52,320
Soon, all of Chae Hwa Young's crimes
will be brought to light.

210
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,180
Grandfather.

211
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:56,150
Please don't be too shocked
when it all comes out.

212
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:20,810
Chae Hwa Young.

213
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:23,550
I will expose every single thing
you've ever done.

214
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:26,550
Seo Rin said she'd give me the evidence
when we meet later,

215
00:17:27,180 --> 00:17:28,820
but I'm sure I can find more
if I look around.

216
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:50,770
(Oh Jang Mi)

217
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:53,310
Why did she write my name
and then cross it out like this?

218
00:17:53,980 --> 00:17:55,280
It's under today's date too.

219
00:17:56,110 --> 00:17:57,750
Is something supposed to happen today?

220
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:01,190
Ma Seo Rin, today's the day.

221
00:18:01,990 --> 00:18:03,420
You're really going to give me
the evidence, right?

222
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:05,890
Yes, I already told you I would.

223
00:18:06,060 --> 00:18:07,930
I'm a woman of my word.

224
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:10,060
See you at that cafe at noon.

225
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:14,260
Okay. But Chae Hwa Young grounded me.

226
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:18,240
- How am I supposed to get out?
- Shit, again?

227
00:18:20,370 --> 00:18:21,770
Don't worry, there's always a way.

228
00:18:22,170 --> 00:18:23,170
How?

229
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:28,980
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

230
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:31,650
I heard there was quite a commotion.

231
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,980
It was nothing I can't handle.

232
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:35,990
Next month's focus will be
on quality control...

233
00:18:35,990 --> 00:18:37,450
for the Food and Beverage
Department's menus...

234
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,860
and conducting intensive
hygiene inspections.

235
00:18:40,490 --> 00:18:44,930
Alright. That's a good idea.
Now that the holiday rush is over,

236
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:47,160
it's time to prepare for the next season.

237
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,200
Yes.

238
00:18:48,470 --> 00:18:50,570
To enhance our hotel's reputation,

239
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,770
we should enter
external culinary competitions...

240
00:18:53,770 --> 00:18:55,270
and add to our list of awards.

241
00:18:55,740 --> 00:18:57,010
That's an excellent idea.

242
00:18:57,880 --> 00:19:02,310
Events like that would be a huge boost
to the hotel's revenue.

243
00:19:04,280 --> 00:19:06,080
Why don't you compete...

244
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:08,050
and sweep the competition?

245
00:19:08,620 --> 00:19:10,020
I need to focus on my duties
as the general manager.

246
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:13,290
I'm planning on sending one
of our junior chefs to the competition.

247
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:15,330
That's our General Manager Kang.

248
00:19:16,130 --> 00:19:18,400
You're so big-hearted,
always looking out for your team.

249
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:22,200
By the way,
I know I've mentioned this before,

250
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:25,400
but you, Seo Rin, and I
should have dinner together.

251
00:19:25,840 --> 00:19:28,070
- What do you say?
- And why would I do that?

252
00:19:28,370 --> 00:19:30,040
There's something I want to talk about.

253
00:19:30,770 --> 00:19:32,010
So make some time for me.

254
00:19:32,810 --> 00:19:33,880
I'd better get back.

255
00:19:43,550 --> 00:19:44,620
My son.

256
00:19:45,220 --> 00:19:46,720
He's just as handsome as ever.

257
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:54,770
Seo Rin?

258
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:21,060
See you next time.

259
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:25,100
I really shouldn't keep seeing you.
I'll get too attached.

260
00:20:25,630 --> 00:20:27,200
I’m going my own way.

261
00:20:28,670 --> 00:20:30,370
Tok Hee is going somewhere.

262
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:34,040
My Tok Hee is so pretty.

263
00:20:34,870 --> 00:20:37,980
I know. I'm very pretty.

264
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:41,240
Mom.

265
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,180
I'll come again.

266
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:48,620
- Is that okay?
- Yes.

267
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:53,060
Tok Hee, you have to come back.
Promise me.

268
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:55,460
I will.

269
00:20:57,930 --> 00:20:59,900
Oh Jang Mi, you've been busy lately.

270
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,630
Where are you off to now?

271
00:21:03,430 --> 00:21:06,440
- Meeting a friend.
- What? You have friends?

272
00:21:06,870 --> 00:21:08,340
I thought all your friends
had given up on you...

273
00:21:08,340 --> 00:21:09,570
since you’re always working.

274
00:21:10,140 --> 00:21:12,810
I do. She's a lot like me, actually.

275
00:21:13,610 --> 00:21:14,610
Anyway,

276
00:21:15,380 --> 00:21:16,580
I'll see you later, Tae Pyung.

277
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:25,990
What's gotten into her?

278
00:21:27,590 --> 00:21:29,860
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

279
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:09,770
Oh Jang Mi just left the house.

280
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:11,900
Good.

281
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:15,010
We can't mess this up, so stay sharp.

282
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:17,040
Yes, boss.

283
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:45,800
Once Seo Rin gets here,

284
00:22:46,300 --> 00:22:49,670
all of your dirty secrets will finally
be exposed, Chae Hwa Young.

285
00:22:50,340 --> 00:22:52,940
The truth about why Seo Rin and I
were forced to live apart,

286
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:57,710
how you managed to steal Seo Rin
and raise her as your own,

287
00:22:58,380 --> 00:23:01,350
and how you framed Baek Ho's father
for my dad's accident...

288
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:02,990
Everything will come to light.

289
00:23:10,290 --> 00:23:13,060
I wonder what kind of evidence
Seo Rin has.

290
00:23:14,230 --> 00:23:15,800
I’m dying to know.

291
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:18,200
What's taking her so long?

292
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:26,680
Seo Rin, where are you?

293
00:23:27,010 --> 00:23:29,380
I'm at the crosswalk
right in front of the cafe now.

294
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:32,620
Just hurry up. I'm dying to know!

295
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:34,280
Shit. You're being so pushy.

296
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:36,450
Should I just turn around?

297
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:37,520
Okay, I'm sorry.

298
00:23:37,990 --> 00:23:39,460
I'll wait.
Just be careful crossing the street.

299
00:23:39,820 --> 00:23:41,290
That's more like it.

300
00:23:44,630 --> 00:23:45,630
Oh, right.

301
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:47,660
I should delete Oh Jang Mi.

302
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:50,870
(Seo Rin, 5 calls)

303
00:23:50,930 --> 00:23:51,940
(You've selected 8)

304
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,000
(Delete 8 items from call log? Delete.)

305
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,000
(No call log)

306
00:24:03,710 --> 00:24:04,780
Take care of Oh Jang Mi.

307
00:24:05,450 --> 00:24:07,020
Make it look like an accident.
Keep it clean.

308
00:24:07,350 --> 00:24:08,420
Oh Jang Mi.

309
00:24:09,290 --> 00:24:11,790
Let's finally end this, once and for all.

310
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:20,500
- Is everything ready?
- Yes, everything is set.

311
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:22,670
Seo Rin is home, right?

312
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:25,370
Yes. We're keeping a close eye on her,
so don't you worry.

313
00:24:26,570 --> 00:24:27,640
Oh Jang Mi.

314
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:29,810
I should have gotten rid of her
a long time ago.

315
00:24:30,710 --> 00:24:32,440
All I did was waste time.

316
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:36,480
It just got poor Oh Bok Gil killed...

317
00:24:37,410 --> 00:24:39,580
and brought the police down on us
for no reason.

318
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,090
There will be no mistakes this time.

319
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:49,630
Oh Jang Mi, you have no idea
what my mother is like.

320
00:24:50,260 --> 00:24:52,260
You have no idea how terrifying she is.

321
00:24:52,530 --> 00:24:55,100
She's not someone you can mess with.

322
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:59,000
That's why you must use the evidence
and report her.

323
00:24:59,570 --> 00:25:01,810
I'm going to tell Grandpa
everything right away.

324
00:25:02,510 --> 00:25:06,480
The only way we even stand a chance
is to strike her at the same time.

325
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:08,980
That's who my mother, Chae Hwa Young, is.

326
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:15,390
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

327
00:25:15,850 --> 00:25:18,860
Shit. Should I answer this or not?

328
00:25:21,190 --> 00:25:22,830
Then again, this could be fun.

329
00:25:26,060 --> 00:25:27,160
Hello?

330
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:29,130
Jang Mi, did you finish your errand?

331
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:31,970
You asked me to drop you off
before we got to your place.

332
00:25:32,300 --> 00:25:34,270
What are you talking about? What errand?

333
00:25:37,070 --> 00:25:38,070
Hello?

334
00:25:38,780 --> 00:25:42,010
You must've called for a reason.
Spit it out!

335
00:25:43,010 --> 00:25:44,210
Is this really Jang Mi?

336
00:25:44,780 --> 00:25:47,520
Why are you so upset again?
I can never get a read on you.

337
00:25:48,080 --> 00:25:49,920
Do I need to take you
to the Han River again?

338
00:25:50,190 --> 00:25:51,520
Do you really need to go back there?

339
00:25:52,790 --> 00:25:53,990
What on earth is he talking about?

340
00:25:57,490 --> 00:26:00,630
I need to cross the street,
and you made me miss the light.

341
00:26:00,960 --> 00:26:02,100
Let's talk later.

342
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,100
Why isn't she crossing?

343
00:26:06,370 --> 00:26:08,170
Oh Jang Mi is on the phone right now.

344
00:26:09,340 --> 00:26:10,970
I can see that, you punk.

345
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:26,220
Why did she write my name
and then cross it out like this?

346
00:26:27,060 --> 00:26:28,360
It's under today's date too.

347
00:26:29,190 --> 00:26:30,530
Is something supposed to happen today?

348
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:39,840
Why did she write my name
in today's date box and then erase it?

349
00:26:41,340 --> 00:26:42,640
What could that mean?

350
00:26:43,970 --> 00:26:46,780
Chae Hwa Young. What are you scheming now?

351
00:26:52,580 --> 00:26:53,650
I have to do something.

352
00:27:02,060 --> 00:27:03,060
Ma Seo Rin!

353
00:27:06,430 --> 00:27:07,430
Shit.

354
00:27:07,430 --> 00:27:08,430
Oh Jang Mi.

355
00:27:09,230 --> 00:27:12,170
Here comes the nag to chew me out
for being late.

356
00:27:13,070 --> 00:27:15,440
How does she feel so familiar
when we've only met a few times?

357
00:27:16,570 --> 00:27:18,040
Is this what family feels like?

358
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:53,840
No!

359
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:13,860
Ma Seo Rin!

360
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:36,720
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
